## Pattern Detection Examples

### Detect Import Patterns
```typescript
// If project uses absolute imports:
import { Button } from '@/components/Button';

// If project uses relative imports:
import { Button } from '../../components/Button';

// If project uses barrel exports:
import { Button, Input, Form } from '@/components';
```

### Detect Testing Patterns
```typescript
// If project uses React Testing Library:
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';

// If project uses Enzyme:
import { mount, shallow } from 'enzyme';

// If project uses Vitest:
import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest';
```

### Detect Error Handling
```typescript
// If project uses try-catch:
try {
  await doSomething();
} catch (error) {
  logger.error('Failed to do something', error);
}

// If project uses Result pattern:
const result = await doSomething();
if (result.isError) {
  return Result.error(result.error);
}
```

